arXiv.abstract:
Motivated by the recent CMS excess in a flavor violating Higgs decay $h ightarrow \mu 	au$ as well as the anomaly of muon anomalous magnetic moment (muon g-2), we consider a scenario where both the excess in $h ightarrow \mu 	au$ and the anomaly of muon g-2 are explained by the $\mu-	au$ flavor violation in a general two Higgs doublet model. We study various processes involving $\mu$ and $	au$, and then discuss the typical predictions and constraints in this scenario. Especially, we find that the prediction of $	au ightarrow \mu \gamma$ can be within the reach of the Belle II experiment. We also show that the lepton non-universality between $	au ightarrow \mu 
u  ar{
u}$ and $	au ightarrow e 
u  ar{
u}$ can be sizable, and hence the analysis of the current Belle data and the future experimental improvement would have an impact on this model. Besides, processes such as $	au ightarrow \mu l^+ l^-~(l=e,~\mu)$, $	au ightarrow \mu \eta$, $\mu ightarrow e \gamma$, $\mu ightarrow 3e$, and muon EDM can be accessible, depending on the unknown Yukawa couplings. On the other hand, the processes like $	au ightarrow e \gamma$ and $	au ightarrow e l^+ l^-~ (l=e,~\mu)$ could not be sizable to observe because of the current strong constraints on the $e-\mu$ and $e-	au$ flavor violations. Then we also conclude that contrary to $h ightarrow \mu 	au$ decay mode, the lepton flavor violating Higgs boson decay modes $hightarrow e \mu$ and $hightarrow e	au$ are strongly suppressed, and hence it will be difficult to observe these modes at the LHC experiment.

We present a detailed analysis and phenomenological consequences of neutrino mass matrix, $M_{
u}$, with one-zero texture in the flavor basis where the active neutrino sector is extended by one sterile neutrino (3+1 case). In particular, our aim is to explore behaviour of the sterile mixing parameters in detail when one of the elements of the neutrino mass matrix goes to zero. To study this, we consider two distinct mass spectrum of the active neutrinos: (i) completely hierarchical mass spectrum with a vanishing neutrino mass and (ii) completely quasidegenerate mass spectrum. In 3+1 scenario, the low energy neutrino mass matrix, $M_{
u}$, is a $4 	imes 4$ matrix and has 10 independent elements. Thus it can have 10 possible one-zero textures. From the earlier studies it can be inferred that, if one assumes one vanishing neutrino mass, then only seven of these $M_{
u}$ are phenomenologically allowed by the current neutrino oscillation data. On the other hand, if the neutrinos are quasidegenerate then there are eight phenomenologically viable one-zero textures. In this present work, we study the correlations between the sterile mixing parameters for each of these allowed textures for both mass spectrum and also their implications on the effective Majorana mass.

Considering the mass splitting between three active neutrinos, we represent the new constraints on the sum of neutrino mass $\sum m_
u$ by updating the anisotropic analysis of Baryon Acoustic Oscillation (BAO) scale in the CMASS and LOWZ galaxy samples from Data Release 12 of the SDSS-III Baryon Oscillation Spectroscopic Survey (BOSS DR12). Combining the BAO data of 6dFGS, MGS, LOWZ and CMASS with $	extit{Planck}$~2015 data of temperature anisotropy and polarizations of Cosmic Microwave Background (CMB), we find that the $95\%$ C.L. upper bounds on $\sum m_
u$ refer to $\sum m_{
u,m NH}<0.18$ eV for normal hierarchy (NH), $\sum m_{
u,m IH}<0.20$ eV for inverted hierarchy (IH) and $\sum m_{
u,m DH}<0.15$ eV for degenerate hierarchy (DH) respectively, and the normal hierarchy is slightly preferred than the inverted one ($\Delta \chi^2\equiv \chi^2_{m NH}-\chi^2_{m IH} \simeq -3.4$). In addition, the additional relativistic degrees of freedom and massive sterile neutrinos are neither favored at present.
